o serves on the house oversight and government reform committee and house natural resources committee. in january 2003, he was elected chairman of the western caucus, a group of more than 50 congressmen working on rational, balanced and sound resource management. </p><p>before his election to congress, congressman cannon was involved in the steel industry. in 1987, he and his brother purchased and reopened geneva steel in orem, ut, restoring 2,500 steel worker jobs. in 1990, he purchased geneva's new venture division, now called cannon industries. he also served in a number of political positions including as utah finance chairman for president george bush's reelection campaign in 1992. he has also served as the utah (PARTY NAME) party's finance chairman and as a delegate to the (PARTY NAME) national conventions in 1992 and 1996. he and his wife, claudia, have eight children and reside in mapleton, ut.</p></span>



